<h2 class="page-title span-24">Consulting</h2>

<div class="span-15 append-1 content-text"><!-- main-col -->
  <p class="large-intro">We advise organizations that need to make intelligent web strategy and infrastructure decisions.</p>
  <p><img src="http://static.gossamer-threads.com/r3/images/office/consulting.jpg" width="590" height="360" alt="Consulting" /></p>

  <h2>Everyone needs reliable tech support</h2>
  <p>
    Many businesses need reliable on-site web technology expertise but
    find it difficult to justify paying full-time wages for this level of
    service. To remedy such situations, we offer ongoing consulting to
    address specific web technology concerns, at a lower overall cost.
  </p>

  <h2>We adapt to your specific needs</h2>
  <p>
    From startups to enterprises, we adapt our services to meet the needs
    of our clients. We have taught some organizations to work with legacy
    IT systems, while others have found it easier to have us take over the
    management of their web-presence, and take on accountability for those
    projects. Our <a href="http://www.gtmetrix.com">GTmetrix</a> tool has led a number of organizations to seek
    us out to assist with optimizing their web properties and help them
    get better performance out of their online technology systems.
  </p>

  <h2>Our clients rely on us for guidance</h2>
  <p>
    Other clients see us as their external team of web experts. They rely
    on us for counsel on how to best define their e-commerce programs,
    improve online communication methods, minimize downtime through
    effective information sharing, examine competitors' web efforts and
    provide insightful analysis.
  </p>

  <h2>We’re in it for the long haul</h2>
  <p>
    Gossamer's consulting services are typically offered on an ongoing
    basis, as this allows us to better understand our clients' long-term
    needs and challenges. That being said, we tailor all programs to meet
    clients' requirements. Some consultations are measured in hours and
    some in days; we're flexible on this point. The important part is that
    we build strong, healthy relationships, in which our clients are
    assured that they are using their web technologies appropriately and
    efficiently.
  </p>



